Torta Caprese
  --America's Test Kitchen
  
6 oz bittersweet chocolate, chopped (60%)
12 tbsp unsalted butter, cut into 12 pieces
1 tsp vanilla
4 eggs, whites and yolks separated
1 c sugar, divided
2 c almond meal (or flour)
2 tbsp dutch process cocoa powder
1/2 tsp salt

Preheat oven to 325F; spray a 9" springform pan with nonstick cooking spray. Place butter and chocolate in a microwave safe bowl and microwave on med power for 1-2 min, stirring occasionally, until all melted. Set aside. Add whites to the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with whisk attachment and beat on medium low until they start breaking up. Increase speed to medium high for a bit, then add 1/2 c sugar and beat on high until glossy and stiff peaks form. Transfer whites to a large bowl and place yolks with remaining 1/2 c sugar in now empty mixer bowl. Start out on medium low, then increase speed to medium high and beat until light and fluffy, ~3-4 min. Add chocolate mixture to yolk mixture and beat to combine, ~15 s. Add almond meal, cocoa, and salt and continue to mix until well incorporated, ~30s. Scrape sides and bottom as needed to ensure everything is incorporated. Add 1/3 of the whites and mix until incorporated. Fold mixture into whites, careful not to loose the lift, until fully incorporated. Pour batter into prepared pan, using spatual to even out and push to sides. Bake for 50 min, or until tester inserted into middle comes out mostly clean. Let cool 20 min on wire rack, then remove the sides of the springform and continue to cool for another 2 hr. Can dust top with powdered sugar before serving if desired.
